## Resources

### Openhatch
OpenHatch is a non-profit dedicated to matching prospective free software contributors with communities, tools, and education.

- **Site:** [https://openhatch.org/](https://openhatch.org/)
- Beginners should probably try out [bite size bugs](http://openhatch.org/search/?q=&toughness=bitesize)

## Projects

### Growstuff
Growstuff is an open source/open data project to create a website for food gardeners.

- **Site:** [http://growstuff.org/](http://growstuff.org/)
- **Repository:** [https://github.com/Growstuff/growstuff](https://github.com/Growstuff/growstuff)
- **Languages:** [Ruby on Rails](http://rubyonrails.org/) ([see their wiki for full list](http://wiki.growstuff.org/index.php/Technology_stack))
- [Newbie Guide](http://wiki.growstuff.org/index.php/Development/Newbie_guide)

### Dreamwidth
Dreamwidth Studios is an Open Source social networking, content management, and personal publishing platform.

- **Site:** [http://www.dreamwidth.org/](http://www.dreamwidth.org/)
- **Repositories:** [https://github.com/dreamwidth/](https://github.com/dreamwidth/)
- **Languages:** Perl, JavaScript  ([see their wiki for full list](http://wiki.dreamwidth.net/wiki/index.php/Dev_Getting_Started#What_you_need))
- [Dev getting started](http://wiki.dreamwidth.net/wiki/index.php/Dev_Getting_Started)

### Django
Django is a high-level Python Web framework that encourages rapid development and clean, pragmatic design.

- **Site:** [https://www.djangoproject.com/](https://www.djangoproject.com/)
- **Repository:** [https://github.com/django/django](https://github.com/django/django)
- **Languages:** [Python](http://www.python.org/)

